VAditya Hrudayam,&#8217; CD released by Oriental Records has Unnikrishnan rendering the slokas set to tune by Rangaswami Parthasarathy in 11 ragas (a raga for three stanzas with the 31st in a different raga).The recital concludes with the last lines of Vishnu Sahasranama, &#8216;Sri Rama Rameti&#8230;&#8217;Earlier works of Rangaswami Parthasarathy, founder of Oriental Records, include Bhagavad Gita, Gayatri Mantra and Valmiki&#8217;s Ramayana.The CD has a booklet containing the slokas (Sanskrit and English transliteration) with meaning.It is distributed by Bharat Records Intl Pvt. Ltd. (28353674, 28351214)
